# Precision Flow — literature map (Phase 0 deliverable)

**Rule (brief, fence 6):** cited mathematics is never re-derived; every entry states
what this campaign uses it for. **Failure behavior, inherited culture restated:**
every instrument failure is a typed/recorded refusal — never a wrong zero, never a
silent skip, never a bound that underflows to 0.0 (Stage-A bigraded lesson).

## PF-1 — Period of the binary expansion of a rational

- **Statement:** for a/b in lowest terms with b = 2^s·b₀ (b₀ odd, b₀ > 1), the
  base-2 expansion of a/b is eventually periodic with pre-period s and minimal
  period **ord₂(b₀)** — the multiplicative order of 2 modulo b₀.
- **Source:** Hardy & Wright, *An Introduction to the Theory of Numbers*, ch. IX
  ("The representation of numbers by decimals", Thms 135–139, stated for general
  base); equivalently Niven–Zuckerman–Montgomery, *An Introduction to the Theory
  of Numbers*, §1.2/§2.x recurring-expansion treatment.
- **Used for:** Stage B's B-P1 — the frozen per-case period values (equality, not
  divisibility). The campaign computes ord₂(b₀) by direct exact arithmetic at
  manifest-freeze time and grades the measured orbit period against it.

## PF-2 — Eventually periodic ⇔ rational

- **Statement:** a real number's base-2 expansion is eventually periodic iff the
  number is rational.
- **Source:** same chapter class as PF-1 (Hardy & Wright ch. IX; standard).
- **Used for:** Stage B's B-P3 — any periodicity detection on the sqrt (irrational)
  battery is an INSTRUMENT DEFECT by this theorem; the prediction polices the
  orbit machinery, not the mathematics.

## PF-3 — Doubling map / Bernoulli shift (framing)

- **Statement:** T(t) = 2t mod 1 on the circle is measurably conjugate to the
  one-sided Bernoulli shift on binary sequences; orbits read off binary digits.
- **Source:** Katok & Hasselblatt, *Introduction to the Modern Theory of Dynamical
  Systems* (Bernoulli shift examples); any standard dynamics text.
- **Used for:** framing ONLY — the Refinement Law's t_{q+1} = 2t_q − D is the
  re-centred doubling map (authority note §1); no dynamical theorem is graded.

## PF-4 — THE FENCE: base-2 normality of algebraic irrationals is OPEN

- **Statement:** whether any algebraic irrational (√2 included) is normal — or
  even has equidistributed binary digits — is a famous open problem (É. Borel 1909, *Les probabilités dénombrables…* — normal numbers
  defined, almost-all-reals-are-normal theorem; the conjecture that algebraic
  irrationals are normal is É. Borel 1950, *C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris* 230,
  591–593, on the digits of √2; no algebraic irrational has been proven normal
  or abnormal in any base; cf. Bailey–Borwein surveys on normality).
- **Used for:** brief non-goal 2. Equidistribution of irrational t-orbits ⇔
  base-2 normality of x. Therefore this campaign NEVER grades a t-distribution,
  never uses "equidistributed" in a verdict, and reports empirical distributions
  as OBSERVATIONAL only. This entry exists so no future reader mistakes the
  fence for ignorance.

## PF-5 — Proto-RG of numerics (framing only, cite-not-claim)

- **Sources:** Richardson 1911 (deferred-approach-to-the-limit extrapolation,
  *Phil. Trans. R. Soc. A* 210); Romberg 1955 (quadrature acceleration);
  Symanzik 1983 (improvement programme, *Nucl. Phys. B* 226 — systematically
  removing cutoff artifacts order by order).
- **Used for:** historical framing of "precision as cutoff, refinement as flow"
  in reports. No content graded; the campaign's own law replaces heuristic
  extrapolation with exact dynamics — that CONTRAST is the only use.

## PF-6 — Discrete scale invariance and log-periodicity (Stage D framing)

- **Source:** D. Sornette, "Discrete scale invariance and complex dimensions",
  *Physics Reports* 297(5) 1998, 239–270.
- **Used for:** Stage D's observational survey vocabulary (DSI, log-periodicity
  with period ln 2). The graded Stage-D claims (D-P1 exact ×2-rescaling
  invariance of t; D-P2 breaking-set containment) are exact symmetry statements
  needing no external theorem; Sornette frames the ungraded survey only.

